Name: Secured Linux Server: Hardening My Ubuntu Server for DevOps Use

Description: This project sets up a secure Ubuntu server for production or DevOps use. It includes firewall rules, SSH security, automatic updates, system logging, and basic monitoringâ€”all automated as much as possible with bash scripts.

Capabilities: Secures SSH access (no password login)

Configures firewall (UFW)

Enables intrusion protection (fail2ban)

Sets up automatic security updates

Installs and configures Nginx (as test reverse proxy)

Automates management with manage.sh menu

Tools / Stack: Ubuntu Server (22.04 LTS recommended)

ufw, fail2ban, unattended-upgrades

ssh, systemd, cron, bash

nginx

Optional: logwatch, rsyslog, netstat
